  "translations": {
    "en": "and bound his hands together to his neck, and called out: O Lord, this is Your servant Bahlul, bound before You. O Lord, You are the One who knows me, and my errors that You know of. O my Master, O Lord, I have become one of the regretful, and I came to Your Prophet repentant, but he sent me away and increased my fear. So I ask You by Your name, Your majesty, and the greatness of Your power, do not diminish my hope, my Master, and do not invalidate my supplication, and do not deprive me of Your mercy. He did not stop saying this for forty days and nights. The wild animals and beasts would weep for him. When forty days and nights had passed, he raised his hands to the sky and said: O Allah, what will You do regarding my need? If You have accepted my supplication and forgiven my sin, then send revelation to Your Prophet. And if You have not accepted my supplication and not forgiven my sin, and You want my punishment, then hasten a fire to burn me or a punishment in this world to destroy me, and deliver me from the disgrace of the Day of Resurrection.",
